<i>noun</i>: 수행자 [수행자], 수도자 [수도자], 도인 [도ː인], 도사 [도ː사] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수행자 [수행자]</dt><br>
<dd>1. trainee; student</dd><br>
<dd>학문이나 무도 등을 닦는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who pursues learning or cultivates chivalry.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ascetic; disciplinant</dd><br>
<dd>부처의 가르침을 실천하기 위해 몸과 마음을 바르게 갈고 닦는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who disciplines himself/herself physically and mentally to put the Buddha's teachings into action.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수도자 [수도자]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ascetic</dd><br>
<dd>도를 닦는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who cultivates himself/herself spiritually or religiously.</dd><br>
<dd>2. monk; nun</dd><br>
<dd>가톨릭에서, 수도사나 수녀.</dd><br>
<dd>A monk or nun in Catholicism.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>도인 [도ː인]</dt><br>
<dd>ascetic</dd><br>
<dd>도를 닦아 큰 이치를 깨달은 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who has found enlightenment through spiritual cultivation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>도사 [도ː사]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ascetic</dd><br>
<dd>도를 닦아 큰 이치를 깨달은 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who has found enlightenment through spiritual cultivation.</dd><br>
<dd>2. dosa</dd><br>
<dd>굿을 하고 점을 치는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>fortune-teller: A person who conducts gut, exorcisms, and tell another's fortune.</dd><br>
<dd>3. master; guru; expert</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 어떤 일에 아주 능숙한 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A person who is very good at doing something.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>